Heat oven to 400 degrees F. Beat egg in large bowl. Add cream cheese; blend well. Add spinach, Swiss cheese, salt, pepper, nutmeg and hot pepper sauce; mix well. Unroll dough onto ungreased cookie sheet. Press to form 12x8-inch rectangle; firmly press perforations to seal. Spoon and spread spinach mixture lengthwise on half of dough. Sprinkle with almonds. Fold untopped half of dough over filling; press edges and ends to seal. Spray top of dough with cooking spray. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 400 degrees F for 18 to 24 minutes or until deep golden brown. Cool 5 minutes. Cut into crosswise slices.